here are the cutoff scores established 
by the 15 states that use the math teacher test developed by the 
educational testing service in princeton nj 
ets grading consists of converting a raw score of the total 
number of correct answers to 150 multiplechoice questions to a 
score on a scale ranging from 250 to 990 this is done 
statistically to account for any variations in the difficulty of 
various versions of the test 
roughly speaking the score of 500 equates to 35 percent and the 
score of 630 equates to 55 percent according to kim kimble an 
administrator of teacher programs and services with ets the median 
score of 540 equates to 40 percent 
arkansas 530 
california 630 
connecticut 580 
