route which includes the entire length of manhattan 
anyone who balks will be physically removed officials said 
the atrain trip takes about 1 hours making it especially 
attractive to people who use the subways which run 24 hours a day 
as a place to sleep 
theres really no problem with sleeping on the trains but we 
cant allow people to sprawl out and take up several seats said 
jared lebow a transit authority spokesman 
he said a worse problem is the behavior of some homeless people 
when they are awakened at the final stop a station where subway 
cars are cleaned and made ready for the return trip 
some of them get pretty upset when the workers try to get them 
to move some of our people have been hit kicked and even spit 
on lebow said 
the new policy follows a crackdown in early june aimed at 
removing hundreds of panhandlers and homeless people from the 
subways and the citys two major rail terminals grand central 
terminal and penn station 
the new effort will be extended next month to another of the 
citys subway routes the e train 
the transit authority said workers from outreach programs will 
assist any homeless people who want to go to shelters 
as with the earlier campaign to displace the displaced from 
grand central and penn stations the latest move prompted a sharp 
reaction from advocates for the homeless 
when are they going to learn moving homeless people from one 
area to another accomplishes nothing said mary brosnahan 
director of the coalition for the homeless when is somebody 
going to stop playing the shell game and work on real solutions to 
the problem 
