the first of more than 3000 
albanian refugees arrived in west germany by train today joyously 
waving their hands in victory as they savored their new freedom 
about 125 albanians reached southern heidelberg aboard a special 
west german train that left basel switzerland after a brief 
stopover en route from italy 
there was no way to live avni azizi a 23yearold albanian 
tailor said of his hardline communist homeland we all think 
that at the most in one year the whole albanian people will be 
free 
the refugees began crowding into foreign embassies in tirana two 
weeks ago seeking to flee albania which has resisted the kinds of 
sweeping democratic reforms that radically altered other east 
european countries since last fall 
about 4500 albanians were evacuated in a sealift across the 
adriatic sea to brindisi italy early friday 
today 56 refugees sheltered in the polish embassy in the 
albanian capital reached warsaw by plane and were taken to an army 
facility northwest of the city 
