<TEXT>
about 30000 years ago an extinct cousin 
of the pig was taking shelter in a cool cave when it slipped at the 
mouth of a 20foot pit and slid in 
indiana state museum workers and volunteers this week followed 
the pig and its mates into two muckfilled cavern rooms that are 
yielding a trove of evidence of prehistoric life in southern 
indiana 
weeklong pig digs over the last four years at mengenity 
peccary cave have unearthed bones of more than 100 examples of the 
nowextinct pig called the flatheaded peccary its the largest 
early peccary find in north america 
sunday is the last day of the annual expedition into the cave to 
root bones out of the sloppy cave floor mud has to be carefully 
troweled from numbered 20inch squares then washed over a screen 
to separate out fragments of bone 
the remains of other animals also have been found in the 
primordial slime of the cave 
its probably the best single time line for ice age life in 
indiana said ron richards the museums curator of paleobiology 
it gives us sort of a history of life in southern indiana over 
the last 30000 years he said every 10 centimeters we dig in 
one cave room takes us back into time as much as 900 years 
richards didnt relish his week in the cave however 
for the most part its cold and damp he said even when 
the temperature outside nears 100 degrees the temperature inside 
seldom climbs above the upper 50s 
they work by the light of kerosene lamps a halfdozen people 
can crowd into the largest room a smaller one holds two or three 
everything you have on is permeated with moisture were 
standing in a couple of inches of water with steam pouring off our 
bodies richards said 
the diggers have found the jaw of a dire wolf now extinct and 
a piece of shell from an ancient tortoise theyve also found 
evidence of arctic shrews plains pocket gophers and rodents 
called yellowcheeked vole 
that shows that it was once a fair amount cooler here he 
said and it shows that at different times there would have been 
grasslands in indiana and prairie 
