in kwazulu and natal province since 1985 leaving more than 4000 
people dead 
both inkatha and the anc oppose apartheid but differ over plans 
for a future south africa inkatha is relatively conservative and 
contends the anc is unjustly trying to claim the role of principla 
negotiator for the black majority 
buthelezi referred to the rivalry with the anc in his speech to 
the party congress 
we will just not allow the anc and its south african communist 
party partner to crush all opposition to it and emerge as the only 
viable political party buthelezi said 
nothing that the anc can do will shake inkathas resolve to 
come out as a new inkatha and a political party to claim its 
rightful place at the negotiating table he said 
the party congress adopted a platform calling for multiparty 
democracy peace and reconciliation education for all south 
africans equality before the law respect for cultural heritage 
and wealth creation to help the underprivileged 
inkatha was formed in 1975 to organize zulus against attempts by 
the south african government to turn the kwazulu homeland into an 
independent state 
buthelezi and his organization successfully resisted the policy 
which would have stripped zulus of their south african citizenship 
inkatha became the dominant political party in the zulu areas and 
runs the homelands semiautonomous government 
the organization claims 15 million members buthelezi has 
described it in the past as a cultural liberation movement but it 
began admitting nonzulus in 1979 
</TEXT>
