more than 7000 in prizes was at stake for hunters in the 
twoday competition billed as a way of reducing the population of 
the foottall grayish brown rodents relatives of the squirrel 
by the end of the hunts first day organizers said 1162 
prairie dogs had been killed way over the maximum 500 predicted 
hunt organizer roger culver attributed the high rate to 
availability of dogs good weather and marksmens skill but added 
that no shooter had hit the 50 dogs allowed 
