wild week of takeover news in the last half of the 1980s 
for one thing there was an absence of junk bonds the risky 
ious used to bankroll many of the highprofile transactions of the 
past decade 
the corporate buyers of 1990 must carry less speculative tools 
like cash stock or secured bank loans partly because attempts to 
peddle junkbond debt to raise takeover money are largely futile 
now the rising number of junkbond defaults has scared most buyers 
away 
another difference in the deals of this past week was that none 
of the buyers were unfriendly outside investors motivated by the 
greedy quick money mentality that colored many other highprofile 
takeovers of the past decade on the contrary all had a direct 
business interest in what they were buying 
the most obvious example also was the biggest not only of the 
