the company has been diligently working to prune those parts 
of the business that have been dragging down our earnings 
campbell told the analysts 
campbell posted a profit of 131 million or 10 cents a share 
in fiscal 1989 on revenues of 567 billion a sharp drop from 
profits of 2741 million or 212 per share on revenues of 487 
billion the year before the decline was due to previous 
restructuring costs 
campbells recent sluggish performance and depressed stock price 
have made it the target of frequent takeover rumors some members 
of the founding dorrance family which owns a major stake have 
urged a sale of the entire company 
over the next few years johnson said campbells plans to boost 
its earnings per share by 20 percent annually he said the company 
also plans to achieve at least a 20 percent return on equity and a 
20 percent cash return on assets 
